PAIN MANAGEMENT CENTER

3
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:11,446
Please...

4
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:13,156
Please...

5
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:16,993
The number you called cannot be reached.

6
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,129
The address is Seongjin-ro 144-2.

7
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:31,382
I think a man has collapsed. Please hurry.

8
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:35,553
Seongjin-ro 144-2? We're on our way.

9
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:37,555
How is the man's condition?

10
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:41,476
-I don't know.
-Sorry? What did you say?

11
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:44,687
I said I don't know!

12
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:48,608
He doesn't know if he's in pain
even when he is!

13
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:50,902
KANG SI-YOUNG

14
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:00,370
He's a CIPA patient.

15
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:03,790
The high temperature
might have given him a fever,

16
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:05,500
so please bring ice packs.

17
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:07,794
Take his temperature
as soon as you find him.

18
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:17,554
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CENTER

19
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:29,399
Where is Dr. Cha--

20
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:32,026
-I mean, where is Cha Yo-han?
-This way, please.

21
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:35,655
He's here.

22
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:42,453
Dr. Cha, are you okay?

23
00:02:44,622 --> 00:02:45,790
I'm fine.

24
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:49,127
-What happened?
-I fell.

25
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:52,505
Anything else? Do you have a fever?

26
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:02,515
You have a fever.

27
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,310
Anything else? Have you done any tests?

28
00:03:06,269 --> 00:03:08,521
Everything else is fine.
It's nothing serious.

29
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:11,524
Are Gi-seok's test results out?

30
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:13,568
Like you predicted, an abscess was found,

31
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:15,403
so we put him on antibiotics.

32
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:17,071
I see.

33
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,741
Dr. Kang called you to tell you that.

34
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,492
You never picked up,
so she called 911.

35
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,494
We were so scared.

36
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:27,749
How is Gi-seok doing?

37
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:31,461
No. Let's go back to the hospital.
We can talk on our way there.

38
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:33,963
No.

39
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,217
You're staying here until your fever goes.

40
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,637
Don't think you can escape like this.

41
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,161
A CERTAIN CHOICE

42
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:19,175
Just a second.

43
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,313
How is he?

44
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:36,067
We need his phlegm test result
to be certain.

45
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,903
But the abscess found on his MRI

46
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,990
is consistent with nocardiosis,
so he's been put on antibiotics.

47
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:44,993
NOCARDIOSIS: LUNG INFECTION COMMON IN
THOSE WITH A WEAKENED IMMUNE SYSTEM

48
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:50,832
Where is Dr. Cha?

49
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:52,041
He's not in the hospital.

50
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,710
He's been excluded from medical duties.

51
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,841
The diagnosis was made by Dr. Cha, right?

52
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:02,635
Is that right?

53
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:07,015
That's right.

54
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,183
He sure is incredible.

55
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:16,316
Yes?

56
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:19,610
The ethics commission has made a decision.

57
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,738
Let's deal with Dr. Cha first,

58
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:24,490
and then you suspend
the life-prolonging treatment for Kang.

59
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:29,454
ETHICS COMMISSION'S DECISION

60
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,956
THERE ARE VALID REASONS ENDING
THE TREATMENT FOR THIS PATIENT

61
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,042
TO LEGITIMATELY SUSPEND
LIFE-PROLONGING TREATMENT...

62
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,464
Losing Dr. Cha...

63
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,550
would be a great loss for us.

64
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:46,512
Even after leaving the hospital,
he focused on diagnosing Lee Gi-seok.

65
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:51,142
So?

66
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:52,935
Chairman Kang...

67
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:56,522
was devoted to producing great doctors.

68
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:59,650
I'm wondering
if we're going against his will.

69
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:04,238
To me, Dr. Cha is a ticking bomb.

70
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:06,491
We've had problems
ever since he joined us.

71
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:09,660
Also, do you want this turmoil to go on?

72
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:12,830
We need to be done with him

73
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:14,707
before we can move on to other matters.

74
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,723
Let's go.

75
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:31,933
I feel completely fine now.

76
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:32,934
Let's go, Si-young.

77
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:41,359
Why hasn't he called yet?

78
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:45,154
It's him.

79
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:46,280
Hold on.

80
00:06:55,415 --> 00:06:57,291
You want to look fine, don't you?

81
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:02,964
Dr. Cha.

82
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,507
Can you see me?

83
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,592
Yes, I can see you.

84
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,599
Gi-seok. It's Dr. Cha. Can you see him?

85
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:17,562
Gi-seok.

86
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:20,773
How do you feel?

87
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:23,609
If you feel okay, blink your eyes once.

88
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,367
You'll recover little by little.

89
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,786
Once your pneumonia gets better,

90
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,414
it'll be easier to breathe.

91
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:38,583
Then you'll be taken off the ventilator.

92
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:42,295
After that, you'll be able
to move your hands and feet.

93
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,091
You'll be able to turn your head, too.

94
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,766
Thanks, Gi-seok.

95
00:07:58,436 --> 00:08:01,606
You must have been frightened,
but you pulled through.

96
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,117
Hang in there.

97
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:18,498
Next time we meet,
I want you to be healthy.

98
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:20,708
Okay?

99
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,174
You can do this, Gi-seok.

100
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:30,384
Stay strong.

101
00:08:48,819 --> 00:08:50,446
Are you wondering why he isn't here?

102
00:08:55,993 --> 00:08:57,286
He'll be here.

103
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:58,871
He will be.

104
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,707
He just needs a little time.

105
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:28,985
Doesn't it hurt?

106
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:33,990
Why would it hurt?

107
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,576
You know it doesn't.

108
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:39,453
It looks like it hurts a lot.

109
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:41,664
Does it?

110
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:44,709
You can say that it hurts.

111
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,587
Please say that it hurts.

112
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,213
You always say you're okay.

113
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:53,384
It must be hard.

114
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:57,972
You're always concerned about me.

115
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,182
You're always anxious.

116
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,477
I'm your guardian, you know.

117
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:06,981
That's my job.

118
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,445
Let's go in.

119
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:17,575
Si-young.

120
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:23,372
Thanks.

121
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:33,841
You once told me

122
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:36,218
you have no idea what you would do...

123
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:39,555
if you ever quit being a doctor.

124
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,642
I just realized

125
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:44,727
that you should treat patients
all your life.

126
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,689
Nothing else would suit you.

127
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:51,025
So, please don't get sick.

128
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,685
DON'T YOU EVER GET SICK

129
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:54,273
DON'T YOU EVER GET SICK

130
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:56,442
Don't you ever get sick.

131
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:23,010
SEOUL HANSE MEDICAL CENTER

132
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:24,929
PAIN MANAGEMENT CENTER

133
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:26,847
It's absurd.

134
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:29,016
How can he treat patients
if he can't feel pain?

135
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:31,560
-A CIPA patient?
-He has a disease.

136
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,229
He's a CIPA patient.

137
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:34,939
Oh, my. I can't believe it.

138
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:36,816
I saw it on Our Famous Doctors.

139
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:40,194
-It's unbelievable.
-He can't feel pain?

140
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:52,706
Gi-seok's phlegm culture
test results just came back.

141
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,416
It's a definite diagnosis. Did you hear?

142
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,252
Yes.

143
00:13:57,211 --> 00:13:59,421
Is Dr. Cha doing okay?

144
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:02,675
He's going to stay home and get some rest.

145
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:06,720
Isn't Dr. Cha working today?

146
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:09,974
No, he won't be treating
any patients for a while.

147
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,016
Why all of a sudden?

148
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:14,603
I came all the way here
from outside the city.

149
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:18,148
I heard Dr. Cha is sick.
Is that really true?

150
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:20,526
What's wrong with him?

151
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,653
He has that illness
where he isn't able to feel pain.

152
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:24,989
Something called
congenital insensitivity...

153
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:26,782
-It's something like that.
-You're done now.

154
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:27,992
-What?
-We'll call you

155
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,034
if you wait outside.

156
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,245
-We're all done here.
-Okay.

157
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:34,081
Please get changed into your patient gown.

158
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:35,082
You may go now.

159
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:36,834
Here you go.

160
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:49,263
What's up?

161
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:52,224
They're gathering a disciplinary
committee for Dr. Cha tomorrow.

162
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:55,853
What? It's tomorrow?

163
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:57,187
That's so fast.

164
00:14:57,271 --> 00:15:00,691
I know. I think they're going to be
pretty tough on him.

165
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,902
Is it normally this easy to fire someone?

166
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:06,071
They'll fire him if he damaged
the hospital's reputation.

167
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:08,574
All they care about
is the hospital's image.

168
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:10,576
Then what should we do?

169
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:13,203
Are we just going to watch
Dr. Cha get fired?

170
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:17,833
Dr. Cha, did you get the summons?

171
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,169
-It's tomorrow.
-I don't need to go, right?

172
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:22,254
Committee's going to gather
even if you don't attend.

173
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,132
If you don't come, you won't get
a chance to explain.

174
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:27,384
-Is that okay with you?
-Yes, it's fine.

175
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:30,304
Okay, I'll call you.

176
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,097
By the way...

177
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:36,393
do you have time today?

178
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:38,103
Today?

179
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:40,356
There's someone I'd like you to meet.

180
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:44,944
Do you remember asking me
who recommended you to this hospital?

181
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:46,820
I want you to meet that person.

182
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:56,413
Hello, how do you feel now?

183
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:57,915
Is it true?

184
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:02,294
Is Dr. Cha really unable to feel pain?

185
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:04,922
-Yes.
-My goodness.

186
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:06,507
That's unbelievable.

187
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:11,303
I really didn't know that about him.

188
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:12,513
Yes.

189
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,974
Dr. Cha has CIPA.

190
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:18,686
But don't you remember
who treated your neuralgia?

191
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:20,145
It was Dr. Cha.

192
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:21,605
He's a very competent doctor--

193
00:16:21,689 --> 00:16:23,482
Yes, exactly.

194
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:26,443
I couldn't even open my mouth properly.

195
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:29,613
And because of that,
I couldn't eat or talk.

196
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:32,408
I went through such a hard time.

197
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:35,202
But how could someone who knows
nothing about pain

198
00:16:35,285 --> 00:16:37,204
treat me so well?

199
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:40,916
He deserves an award for that.

200
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:44,545
When is he planning to return?

201
00:16:44,628 --> 00:16:48,465
I'd love to thank him myself.

202
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:51,218
I should thank you.

203
00:16:52,386 --> 00:16:53,637
Thank you so much, sir.

204
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:57,266
I want everyone to come inside. Hurry.

205
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,611
-I think I know how we can help Dr. Cha.
-How?

206
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:11,530
-Really?
-How can we help?

207
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:15,868
I'm going to divide you into two teams.

208
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:22,374
-Here you go.
-Please fill in the form.

209
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,376
You know Dr. Cha, right?

210
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:33,343
Can you please give this a read?

211
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:35,804
Once you're done reading it,
there's a survey...

212
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:39,224
Really? Okay, thank you.

213
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:41,310
Okay, bye.

214
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:16,887
Sir, Dr. Cha is here.

215
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:30,692
Hello, my name is Cha Yo-han.

216
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:33,195
I've always wanted to meet you.

217
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:35,572
Take a seat.

218
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:38,450
Sit down.

219
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:58,428
Why did you want to see me, sir?

220
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:01,974
At first, you probably wanted
to become a doctor

221
00:19:02,057 --> 00:19:04,685
so you could find out more
about your own illness,

222
00:19:04,768 --> 00:19:06,645
not because you wanted to treat patients.

223
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,191
I felt the same way.

224
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:15,320
I wanted to know more
about this illness I had,

225
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:18,490
which caused my muscles
and organs to get stiff.

226
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:22,452
And I wanted to find a way to cure it.

227
00:19:23,328 --> 00:19:25,873
However, I failed.

228
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:29,168
Instead, I was able to come across
another method.

229
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:32,963
I found a way...

230
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,758
to get rid of the pain
instead of the illness itself.

231
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:43,307
Don't you want to know what that is?

232
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:47,477
Show him.

233
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:57,988
Hello.

234
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,618
Nurse.

235
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:04,703
May I help you?

236
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:08,832
Is there a clinical trial for people
who have terminal cancer?

237
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:14,630
The thing is, my sister
got this text yesterday.

238
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,301
There's going to be a presentation

239
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:21,678
regarding clinical trials
for patients with terminal cancer.

240
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:24,097
I'll see you tomorrow at 5:00 p.m.
at Death Talks.

241
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:25,599
DEATH TALKS

242
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:27,559
Death Talks.

243
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:29,811
Isn't this the gathering
you attended yesterday?

244
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:31,521
Death Talks?

245
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:38,737
THE BRAIN WAVES STARTED AT BETA
AND DISPLAYED THETA

246
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:47,621
IT FLATLINED AND MS. PARK HYUN-SOOK
PASSED AWAY PEACEFULLY

247
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:51,416
CHERUBIM PROMISES YOU A PAINLESS ENDING

248
00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:55,754
What do you think?

249
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:21,989
Is this the police?

250
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:25,993
There's a murderer here.

251
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:29,579
Not only did he conspire to murder,

252
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:31,123
but he also committed murder.

253
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:36,128
What if I reported you to the police
for having killed my patient?

254
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:38,922
Why are you showing this to me?

255
00:21:41,591 --> 00:21:43,302
"Murder"?

256
00:21:43,385 --> 00:21:45,595
If this isn't murder,
do you think this is salvation?

257
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,764
"Salvation"?

258
00:21:49,891 --> 00:21:53,186
What's the big deal about death?

259
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:56,273
Everyone dies.

260
00:21:57,566 --> 00:22:02,904
But not everyone can die in peace.

261
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:04,656
No one in this world...

262
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:07,534
can avoid death.

263
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:12,831
So, why is it so bad
to want to die in peace?

